Here we list the known problems with compiler (and system) configurations and possible solutions if there are some.
When we edit we add the date.

============================================================================================
Revision History

first notes: Kristina Froehlich, MPI-M 2011-05-25

============================================================================================

SYSTEMS

32-bit maschines are not recommended to use for developing purposes, since the model is too big and needs too much memory that might cause trouble.


COMPILERS

1) gcc

2)NAG

 is not able to generate grids. Please run first the gcc to create grids

3) intel
 known to show up stacksize problems

4) PGI
 possible compilation bug with regard to bounds?



